      <!--Content Left start-->
      <div class="content-left">
       <div class="service-text-part">
        <p>
         Save Home Health Care, Inc. provides a variety of skilled and specialized services. We strive to provide you with whatever home care services you require for a better lifestyle.
         <br />
         <br />
        </p>
        <h1>
         Skilled Nursing Care - RN's, LVN's
        </h1>
        <p>
         Our nurses have only one thing in mind: The Patient.  SHHC's highly trained nurses are the best in the business.  Our certified nurses promise to provide our patients with professional health care managment. SHHC has a variety of Registered Nurses and Licensed Vocational Nurses staffed to aide in the patient's home health needs.
        </p>
        <p>
        </p>
        <h1>
         IV Therapy
        </h1>
        <p>
         Intravenous therapy or IV therapy is the giving of liquid substances directly into a vein. It can be intermittent or continuous; continuous administration is called an intravenous drip. The word intravenous simply means "within a vein", but is most commonly used to refer to IV therapy. Compared with other routes of administration, the intravenous route is the fastest way to deliver fluids and medications throughout the body. We provide patients and their family with the knowledge needed to properly and successfully administrate an IV.
        </p>
        <h1>
        </h1>
        <h1>
         Tube Feedings
        </h1>
        <p>
         Nutrients, either a special liquid formula or pureed food, are delivered to a patient through a tube directly into the gastrointestinal tract, usually into the stomach or small intestine.  Our highly trained nursing staff will provide proper education and assistance to the patients tube feeding needs.
        </p>
        <h1>
        </h1>
        <h1>
         Wound Care/Digital Imaging
        </h1>
        <p>
         We keep patients updated on today's most advance wound care techniques.  We promise to provide the patient with properly administered wound care.  We know that faster healing leads to a better lifestyle.
        </p>
        <p>
         With the advent of technology, we are now able to expedite coordination of care.  With Wound Site Digital Imaging, we can send the image digitally over the internet quickly and securely.  The doctor is now able to instantly determine the steps to help our patients heal faster.
        </p>
        <h1>
        </h1>
        <h1>
         Medical Social Services
        </h1>
        <p>
         SHHC Medical social workers (MSW) are trained to help individuals, couples and families deal with the social, cultrual, and psychological medical issues resulting from an illness. Our MSW's help patients fully utilize medical care and services through proper education and training.  Our Medical social workers will help patients with advance directives and other long-term care issues. They assure that patientsâ€™ medically related emotional and social needs are met and maintained throughout their medical treatment.
        </p>
        <br />
        <h1>
        </h1>
        <h1>
         Physical Therapy
        </h1>
        <p>
         SHHC contracts South Texas' best physical therapists.  Our physical therapists are certified to meet a variety of theraputic needs for the patient. Our staff will coordinate closely with the contracted therapist, assuring that the services are dependable and the patient's recovery, fast.
        </p>
        <h1>
        </h1>
        <h1>
         Occupational Therapy
        </h1>
        <p>
         For some patient's, their health problems limit them to performing some of their everyday essential tasks. Our Occupational Therapists are here the help patients and their families achieve a healthy and balanced life through life-style improvements and family awareness.
        </p>
        <h1>
        </h1>
        <h1>
         Speech Therapy
        </h1>
        <p>
         Sometimes a health condition can affect a patient's speech. Communication is important and we are here to provide patients with the therapy needed to continue on with their lives.
        </p>
        <h1>
        </h1>
        <h1>
         Anodyne Therapy
        </h1>
        <p>
         Anodyne Therapy provides pain relief using infrared light. This therapy is good for treating pain, circulatory problems, stiffness and more.
        </p>
        <h1>
        </h1>
        <h1>
         Vital Stim
        </h1>
        <p>
         Vital Stim Therapy is used for patients who suffer from dysphagia. Dysphagia is a condition that causes difficulty in swallowing.
        </p>
        <p>
         Other skilled services are also available. Please contact the SHHC at 361-855-9393 for more information.
        </p>
        <p>
        </p>
       </div>
